<br>
Also, could I do dervs in IC?  I have over 200 int (Should have put more into STR).  Also have some ok mana items.  2 plat imbued rings and a crystal web shield (Think it's about 110 mana).  I have my staff, and a friendly shaman that gives me a discount on SoW potions.  Possible to do?<br>
<br>
Thanks!!!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 9:10:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question..</span><hr size=1> Conventional Wisdom is:<br>
<br>
Do not quad real casters.<br>
<br>
Even ranger types can ruin your day with a root or snare.<br>
<br>
Mobs like specs that have a inherent short range spell are doable, if a little more tricky, but true casters are too much trouble. Not a reliable way to get xp, IMO.<br>
<br>
If you feel you need treant faction for some reason, just go quad for xp until you get an ae that can massacre a whole bandit camp in one cast and fix it then.<br>
<br>
FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/31/01 11:13:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question..</span><hr size=1> Also, I would not try to quad anything that does not result in a faction hit. The reason being is that if mobs are on the same faction, they will continue to attack until they are dead if they have friends with them. Non faction mobs tend to run when they get low HP resulting in a messy clean up.<br>
<br>
If you want to quad in IC do wolves or cougars. Make sure you have the mana before you try, I think they have about 1200hp or so. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 45th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p>
<span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 22 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvespid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vespid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/1/01 6:41:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question..</span><hr size=1> Vespid's QK Tips:<br>
<br>
1. When learning a new mob, always start with a single to test your technique.  Flux it and get out of spellcasting range (that tests their foot speed), snare it, then proceed to nuke it down.<br>
<br>
2. If mobs are not quite stacked together, running in circles isn't necessary.  Try running away from the mobs making large S patterns as you go -- they round up sweetly and there isn't any chance of cutting the circle a little too close.<br>
<br>
3. Always snare them after they have been rounded up -- a mana bar is a terrible thing to waste.<br>
<br>
